column5: Well after yesterdays battle with the whitefish me and meely decided to give it another go,  we even took my old man for his first crack at soft water whities.  We tried all the spots that we hauled them in yesterday but the action was SLOW.  2 fish caught and we only had a few bumps.  So out we went in search!  We broke away from the pack and found some fish holding in about 80fow.  williams put most of our fish in the boat but the bad boy did well too.   It wasnt as good as yesterday but we did get our limit and also live released a few others!   back at my cleaning station

Way to go guys !!!  Uncle Dave showed up around noon to pick up his boat...after we got it all hooked up we took a run over to (you know where) and managed a few crappies and 'gills...no great sizes but fun to catch...
Congrats, nice job on hunting them down
Good to hear you and your Dad finally found em
its always nice to see the old man nail a few
got to love somcoe  you are going to need a bigger freezer
they sure are tasty and dont last to long in my house lol
congrats on your day, thanks for the info
love those whities..simcoe is a great lake...
